Author:
Vol / Page: 2/16
Edition:
Quote:  [The dam] looked well for a good `drive,' and the boss gave the word to `trip' it and let her go as soon as the logs were straightened up.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1913
Source: NZ Geol. Survey Bulletin
Author:
Vol / Page: No.16 (NS) 27
Edition:
Quote: During a `drive' the logs, driven by the rush of the waters, scour out the bottoms of the creeks, and create artificial floods, by which logs, dragged to the creeks, may be transported.
Notes: (Henderson and Bartrum, Aroha and Hauraki)

